thread.title: Residents in Gaylord dig out of another winter storm
thread.title_full: Residents in Gaylord dig out of another winter storm

author: Audrey Boucher | UpNorthLive Newsroom
title: Residents in Gaylord dig out of another winter storm
text: OTSEGO COUNTY, Mich. (WPBN/WGTU) -- Gaylord residents spent Thursday digging out of another winter storm. So far this season Gaylord has dealt with two major winter storm systems, one of them was a record setter. Forecast: Lake effect snow comes to end, some areas will see some sun Friday Joshua Burleson said after a snow storm it can take him almost two hours to clear his driveway, especially when wind is also a factor. Road Crews: County road commission crews kept busy amid early season storms The area has dealt with nearly 42 inches of snowfall so far this season. “The snow that we got so far is say it’s more than what we got last year. I think I used my snow blower a total of four times last year and this year it’s already been ten plus times,\" said Burleson. After Burleson cleared his own driveway Thursday, he went across the street to help his elderly neighbor by clearing their driveway as well.
